name: mehulumistry/Query-Processing-Engine
description: Building a Query Processing Engine for ad-hoc OLAP queries based on Extended-SQL syntax known as Multi-Feature Queries and Extended Multi-Feature Queries (MF and EMF Queries) which provide a simple, efficient and scalable algorithm for processing queries. Originally, ad-hoc OLAP queries, when expressed in standard SQL lead to very complex relational algebraic expressions, which in turn leads to inefficient optimization and hence poor performance.  The query processing engine takes Extended-SQL queries as input and processes them to generate a java file. The java file thus generated produces the output of the query from the database.
